jnxLdp.name: jnxLdp

revisions.description: Added 'jnxLdpInstanceName' to the jnxLdpLspUp and jnxLdpLspDown trap.
Modified description of jnxLdpSesDownIf and jnxLdpSesDown.

jnxLdp.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxLdp.description: The MIB modules extends the LDP mib draft.

jnxLdpLspFec.name: jnxLdpLspFec
jnxLdpLspFec.description: The LSP FEC in IP address format.

jnxLdpRtrid.name: jnxLdpRtrid
jnxLdpRtrid.description: The router id of the sending router.

jnxLdpLspDownReason.name: jnxLdpLspDownReason
jnxLdpLspDownReason.description: The reason why the LSP went down. Can be one of the following: the topology changed, the neighbor withdrew the label, the neighbor went down, the filter changed, the BFD session went down, lsping down, or the reason is unknown.

jnxLdpSesDownReason.name: jnxLdpSesDownReason
jnxLdpSesDownReason.description: The reason why the session transitioned to nonexistent state. Can be one of the following: unknown reason, hold time expired, connection time expired, all adjacencies down, received bad tlv, received bad pdu, connectionn error, connection reset, received notification from peer, received unexpected end-of-file, authentication key was changed, error during initialization, graceful restart was aborted or cli command.

jnxLdpSesDownIf.name: jnxLdpSesDownIf
jnxLdpSesDownIf.description: This variable is the snmp index of the interface relevant to the session-down event. If no interface can be correlated to the session-down, then it is the interface associated with one of the neighbors.

jnxLdpLspFecLen.name: jnxLdpLspFecLen
jnxLdpLspFecLen.description: The length in bits of the LSP FEC prefix.

jnxLdpSesUpIf.name: jnxLdpSesUpIf
jnxLdpSesUpIf.description: This variable is the interface index of one of the neighbors associated with this session.

jnxLdpLspUp.name: jnxLdpLspUp
jnxLdpLspUp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an LSP comes up.

jnxLdpLspDown.name: jnxLdpLspDown
jnxLdpLspDown.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the LSP goes down.

jnxLdpSesUp.name: jnxLdpSesUp
jnxLdpSesUp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the value of 'jnxMplsLdpSesState' enters the 'operational(5) state.

jnxLdpSesDown.name: jnxLdpSesDown
jnxLdpSesDown.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the value of 'jnxMplsLdpSesState' leaves the 'operational(5) state. The value of jnxLdpSesDownIf is one of the neighbor's interface. It is the interface associated with the last neighbor when jnxLdpSesDownReason is allAdjacenciesDown (3).

jnxLdpStatsTable.name: jnxLdpStatsTable
jnxLdpStatsTable.description: Table of statistics of Ldp FECs.

jnxLdpStatsEntry.name: jnxLdpStatsEntry
jnxLdpStatsEntry.description: Entry containing statistics information about a particular LDP FEC.

jnxLdpFecStatisticsStatus.name: jnxLdpFecStatisticsStatus
jnxLdpFecStatisticsStatus.description: Indicates the status of traffic statistics for this FEC. For penultimate hop FECs traffic statistics can be disabled. For such FECs, the following objects will have the value '0'.

jnxLdpIngressOctets.name: jnxLdpIngressOctets
jnxLdpIngressOctets.description: The number of octets of traffic originated on this box, forwarded over the current LDP FEC. The number reported is not realtime and may be subject to several minutes delay. The delay is controllable by ldp statistics gathering interval, which by default is 5 minutes.

jnxLdpIngressPackets.name: jnxLdpIngressPackets
jnxLdpIngressPackets.description: The number of packets of traffic originated on this box, forwarded over the current LDP FEC. The number reported is not realtime and may be subject to several minutes delay. The delay is controllable by ldp statistics gathering interval, which by default is 5 minutes.

jnxLdpTransitOctets.name: jnxLdpTransitOctets
jnxLdpTransitOctets.description: The number of octets of traffic destined to this FEC, originated on a different box, forwarded over the current LDP FEC. The number reported is not realtime and may be subject to several minutes delay. The delay is controllable by ldp statistics gathering interval, which by default is 5 minutes.

jnxLdpTransitPackets.name: jnxLdpTransitPackets
jnxLdpTransitPackets.description: The number of packets of traffic destined to this FEC, originated on a different box, forwarded over the current LDP FEC. The number reported is not realtime and may be subject to several minutes delay. The delay is controllable by ldp statistics gathering interval, which by default is 5 minutes.
